<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-487] Generated SUBSTRING SQL is ugly and inefficient</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-487</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When performing a JPQL query with a SUBSTRING clause, OpenJPA converts from one-based index + length parameters to zero-based index + end index for internal handling, and then re-converts back to one-based + length when generating SQL. This conversion is entirely performed in query values, so the generated SQL has a lot of math in it. This extra math is never necessary.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12386334">OPENJPA-487</key>
            <summary>Generated SUBSTRING SQL is ugly and inefficient</summary>
